{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A request whose signature does not match its body is rejected with a 401 response; the body is not forwarded.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is handler+middleware+queue handoff: signature must be checked against the raw body, then queue write must not happen. A pure unit test of a verifier function would miss raw-body plumbing bugs. Rejected higher levels: no real OS/network/subprocess requirement beyond in-process app wiring (so not System), no AI output dependency (not Agentic/Workflow).","test_description":"Run the HTTP handler with real request-body parsing/middleware wiring and a test queue implementation. Send a request with mismatched HMAC header/body, assert 401, and assert zero enqueue attempts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"An event is written to the persistent queue before the HTTP 200 acknowledgment is returned to the sender.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is an ordering guarantee across modules (HTTP handler and persistent queue). Need real queue persistence component (e.g., local DB/file-backed queue module) to catch ack-before-durable-write regressions. Rejected higher levels: no real external network/subprocess dependency required, and no AI dependency.","test_description":"Wire handler to the real persistent queue module in test mode. Instrument queue write completion and response send time; assert durable write completes before 200 response is emitted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The handler returns the HTTP response without waiting for downstream processing of the event to finish.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is async